#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:1
msgid "Cache-DiT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:3
msgid ""
"SGLang integrates [Cache-DiT](https://github.com/vipshop/cache-dit), a "
"caching acceleration engine for Diffusion Transformers (DiT), to achieve up "
"to **1.69x inference speedup** with minimal quality loss."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "概覽"

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:7
msgid ""
"**Cache-DiT** uses intelligent caching strategies to skip redundant "
"computation in the denoising loop:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:9
msgid ""
"**DBCache (Dual Block Cache)**: Dynamically decides when to cache "
"transformer blocks based on residual differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:10
msgid ""
"**TaylorSeer**: Uses Taylor expansion for calibration to optimize caching "
"decisions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:11
msgid ""
"**SCM (Step Computation Masking)**: Step-level caching control for "
"additional speedup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:13
msgid "Basic Usage"
msgstr "基礎用法"

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:15
msgid ""
"Enable Cache-DiT by exporting the environment variable and using `sglang "
"generate` or `sglang serve` :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:17
msgid ""
"SGLANG_CACHE_DIT_ENABLED=true \\\n"
"sglang generate --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"    --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:23
msgid "Diffusers Backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:25
msgid ""
"Cache-DiT supports loading acceleration configs from a custom YAML file. For "
"diffusers pipelines (`diffusers` backend), pass the YAML/JSON path via `--"
"cache-dit-config`. This flow requires cache-dit >= 1.2.0 (`cache_dit."
"load_configs`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:29
msgid "Single GPU inference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:31
msgid "Define a `cache.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:33
msgid "DBCache + TaylorSeer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:35
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:48
msgid "Then apply the config with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:50
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config cache.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:58
msgid "DBCache + TaylorSeer + SCM (Step Computation Mask)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:60
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
"  # Must set the num_inference_steps for SCM. The SCM will automatically\n"
"  # generate the steps computation mask based on the num_inference_steps.\n"
"  # Reference: https://cache-dit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user_guide/"
"CACHE_API/#scm-steps-computation-masking\n"
"  num_inference_steps: 28\n"
"  steps_computation_mask: fast\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:78
msgid "DBCache + TaylorSeer + SCM (Step Computation Mask) + Cache CFG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:80
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
"  num_inference_steps: 28\n"
"  steps_computation_mask: fast\n"
"  enable_sperate_cfg: true # e.g, Qwen-Image, Wan, Chroma, Ovis-Image, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:96
msgid "Distributed inference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:98
msgid "1D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:100
msgid ""
"Define a parallelism only config yaml `parallel.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:102
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:108
msgid ""
"Then, apply the distributed inference acceleration config from yaml. "
"`ulysses_size: auto` means that cache-dit will auto detect the `world_size` "
"as the ulysses_size. Otherwise, you should manually set it as specific int "
"number, e.g, 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:110
msgid ""
"Then apply the distributed config with: (Note: please add `--num-gpus N` to "
"specify the number of gpus for distributed inference)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:112
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --num-gpus 4 \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config parallel.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A futuristic cityscape at sunset\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:121
msgid "2D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:123
msgid ""
"You can also define a 2D parallelism config yaml `parallel_2d.yaml` file "
"that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:125
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  tp_size: 2\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:131
msgid ""
"Then, apply the 2D parallelism config from yaml. Here `tp_size: 2` means "
"using tensor parallelism with size 2. The `ulysses_size: auto` means that "
"cache-dit will auto detect the `world_size // tp_size` as the ulysses_size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:133
msgid "3D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:135
msgid ""
"You can also define a 3D parallelism config yaml `parallel_3d.yaml` file "
"that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:137
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: 2\n"
"  ring_size: 2\n"
"  tp_size: 2\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:144
msgid ""
"Then, apply the 3D parallelism config from yaml. Here `ulysses_size: 2`, "
"`ring_size: 2`, `tp_size: 2` means using ulysses parallelism with size 2, "
"ring parallelism with size 2 and tensor parallelism with size 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:146
msgid "Ulysses Anything Attention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:148
msgid ""
"To enable Ulysses Anything Attention, you can define a parallelism config "
"yaml `parallel_uaa.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:150
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  ulysses_anything: true\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:157
msgid "Ulysses FP8 Communication"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:159
msgid ""
"For device that don't have NVLink support, you can enable Ulysses FP8 "
"Communication to further reduce the communication overhead. You can define a "
"parallelism config yaml `parallel_fp8.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:161
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  ulysses_float8: true\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:168
msgid "Async Ulysses CP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:170
msgid ""
"You can also enable async ulysses CP to overlap the communication and "
"computation. Define a parallelism config yaml `parallel_async.yaml` file "
"that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:172
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  ulysses_async: true # Now, only support for FLUX.1, Qwen-Image, Ovis-Image "
"and Z-Image.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:178
msgid ""
"Then, apply the config from yaml. Here `ulysses_async: true` means enabling "
"async ulysses CP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:180
msgid "TE-P and VAE-P"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:182
msgid ""
"You can also specify the extra parallel modules in the yaml config. For "
"example, define a parallelism config yaml `parallel_extra.yaml` file that "
"contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:184
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:192
msgid "Hybrid Cache and Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:194
msgid ""
"Define a hybrid cache and parallel acceleration config yaml `hybrid.yaml` "
"file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:196
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:213
msgid ""
"Then, apply the hybrid cache and parallel acceleration config from yaml."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:215
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --num-gpus 4 \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config hybrid.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:224
msgid "Attention Backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:226
msgid ""
"In some cases, users may want to only specify the attention backend without "
"any other optimization configs. In this case, you can define a yaml file "
"`attention.yaml` that only contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:228
msgid "attention_backend: \"flash\" # '_flash_3' for Hopper\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:232
msgid "Quantization"
msgstr "量化"

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:234
msgid ""
"You can also specify the quantization config in the yaml file, required "
"`torchao>=0.16.0`. For example, define a yaml file `quantize.yaml` that "
"contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:236
msgid ""
"quantize_config: # quantization configuration for transformer modules\n"
"  # float8 (DQ), float8_weight_only, float8_blockwise, int8 (DQ), "
"int8_weight_only, etc.\n"
"  quant_type: \"float8\"\n"
"  # layers to exclude from quantization (transformer). layers that contains "
"any of the\n"
"  # keywords in the exclude_layers list will be excluded from quantization. "
"This is useful\n"
"  # for some sensitive layers that are not robust to quantization, e.g., "
"embedding layers.\n"
"  exclude_layers:\n"
"    - \"embedder\"\n"
"    - \"embed\"\n"
"  verbose: false # whether to print verbose logs during quantization\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:248
msgid ""
"Then, apply the quantization config from yaml. Please also enable torch."
"compile for better performance if you are using quantization. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:250
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --warmup \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config quantize.yaml \\\n"
"  --enable-torch-compile \\\n"
"  --dit-cpu-offload false \\\n"
"  --text-encoder-cpu-offload false \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:262
msgid "Combined Configs: Cache + Parallelism + Quantization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:264
msgid ""
"You can also combine all the above configs together in a single yaml file "
"`combined.yaml` that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:266
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  attention_backend: native\n"
"  extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
"quantize_config:\n"
"  quant_type: \"float8\"\n"
"  exclude_layers:\n"
"    - \"embedder\"\n"
"    - \"embed\"\n"
"  verbose: false\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:288
msgid ""
"Then, apply the combined cache, parallelism and quantization config from "
"yaml. Please also enable torch.compile for better performance if you are "
"using quantization."
msgstr ""

